1 olive oil
1 bag peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet sesame seeds
2 clove garlic
1 tbs soy sauce
1 stalk celery
1 packet pork schnitzels
1 tsp plain flour
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over sesame seeds. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. In a small bowl, combine garlic and the soy sauce.
• When the pumpkin has 5 minutes remaining, remove tray from the oven, then spoon the soy-garlic mixture over pumpkin. Roast until tender and caramelised, 5 minutes.

• While the pumpkin is roasting, thinly slice celery.
• Separate pork schnitzels (if stuck together) to get two per person.
• In a shallow bowl, whisk the plain flour, sweet soy seasoning and the egg until combined. In a second shallow bowl, place panko breadcrumbs and a
pinch of salt.
• Coat pork first in the egg mixture, followed by the breadcrumbs. Set aside on a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base.
• When oil is hot, cook crumbed pork in batches until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and season with a pinch of salt.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, celery, ponzu sauce and a drizzle of olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.
• Divide sweet-soy crumbed pork, sesame roasted pumpkin and ponzu slaw between bowls. Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the ingredients for the slaw.